Hmmm.  In that case, we've got something else going on!

I installed ideviceinstaller (though it sounds like it's not needed) and restarted IntelliJ, community. Still seeing the same issue. (And I should have mentioned that the stop button doesn't light up, either, but I see you mentioned it.)
When trying to repro this locally, it looks like IntelliJ loses the debug connection; not yet sure why.
Yes, the simulator continues to show the last app you ran, even if you've quit IntelliJ. It does suggest that connectivity is toast.
(this is likely a regression in the flutter_tools deamon launch mode)

From a bisect, it looks like we broke at this commit: https://github.com/flutter/flutter/commit/f888bbed48e36d03bb78cb3e7a6e124b32748356

I'll dig into that change
Great! @Sfshaza, you can get the fix by running `flutter upgrade` from the command-line.
It's working for me now! Thanks for fixing it so promptly!
